BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
PRODID:10k-sub40-by-june-2026-v4
CALSCALE:GREGORIAN
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260419
SUMMARY:Long Run Easy (16-18 km\, no steady finish)
DESCRIPTION:Run 16-18 km easy and conversational. First 20-30 min deliberately easy. Keep HR mostly 135-150; okay briefly to 152 late only if pace still feels relaxed. No steady finish. If wind or hills push HR up\, slow down and protect effort. Goal = finish feeling you could keep going 10-15 more min.
UID:20260419-63@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260421
SUMMARY:Aerobic Support Run + Strides (60-70 min easy)
DESCRIPTION:60-70 min easy. First 20 min very easy. Keep HR mostly 135-148. If you feel excellent\, final 15-20 min may drift to HR 150-156\, but never turn this into a steady grind. Add 4-6x20s relaxed strides only if legs feel good. Priority = be fresh for Thursday.
UID:20260421-64@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260423
SUMMARY:Goal-Pace Blocks (3x2 km controlled 10K effort)
DESCRIPTION:Warm-up 20 min easy (HR 135-150\, ~5:00-5:40/km) + 4 strides. Main: 3x2 km at controlled 10K effort. Start rep 1 around ~4:03-4:05/km; reps 2-3 may move toward ~4:00-4:03/km only if breathing stays controlled and form is relaxed. Recover with 2:30-3:00 easy jog (not walk)\, letting HR come down toward <155. Cool-down 10-15 min easy. Success = even effort\, not forcing 3:59 from the start.
UID:20260423-65@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260425
SUMMARY:Easy + Strides (Optional) (35-50 min easy)
DESCRIPTION:Optional recovery run: 35-50 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:05-5:50/km) + 4-6x20s relaxed strides with full walk/jog recovery. Skip if fatigue is high or if Thursday still lingers in the legs.
UID:20260425-66@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260426
SUMMARY:Long Run Easy (18-20 km\, no steady finish)
DESCRIPTION:Run 18-20 km easy. First 20-30 min very easy. Keep HR mostly 135-150; okay briefly to 152 late only if still conversational. No steady finish in this block. Because your recent weekly volume is mostly in the low-40s km\, this run should support the plan\, not dominate it.
UID:20260426-67@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260428
SUMMARY:Easy + Strides (Deload) (45-55 min easy)
DESCRIPTION:Deload: 45-55 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:05-5:50/km) + 4-6x20s relaxed strides with full recovery. Keep the whole session light and snappy.
UID:20260428-68@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260430
SUMMARY:Easy Fartlek (Deload) (8x1 min on / 1 min off)
DESCRIPTION:Warm-up 15 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:05-5:45/km). Main: 8x(1 min on at controlled 10K effort / 1 min off easy jog). On flat calm ground the on-segments may land around ~4:00-4:10/km\, but use feel if windy. Cool-down 10-15 min easy. Finish feeling springy\, not cooked.
UID:20260430-69@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260503
SUMMARY:Long Run Cutdown (Deload) (14-16 km easy)
DESCRIPTION:Deload long run: 14-16 km easy and conversational (HR 135-150\, ~5:05-5:45/km). No steady finish. Keep it clearly easier than a normal long run.
UID:20260503-70@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260505
SUMMARY:Threshold-Lite (2x15 min by HR/RPE)
DESCRIPTION:Warm-up 20 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:05-5:45/km) + 4 strides. Main: 2x15 min at controlled threshold-lite\, HR mostly 168-174\, RPE about 7/10. On a flat calm day this may land around ~4:18-4:28/km\, but do not force pace if windy or rolling. 3 min easy jog between reps\, HR ideally down toward the low 150s. Cool-down 10-15 min easy. Finish feeling like you could do a few more minutes if needed.
UID:20260505-71@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260507
SUMMARY:5K Benchmark Time Trial (paced\, not heroic)
DESCRIPTION:Warm-up 20 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:05-5:45/km) + drills + 4 strides. Main: 5 km hard but paced. Open controlled: first 1-2 km no faster than ~3:58-4:00/km\, then settle by feel. Use this as a checkpoint\, not a make-or-break day. If legs feel flat from Tuesday\, replace with 4x1 km at controlled 10K effort with 2 min easy jog. Cool-down 15 min easy.
UID:20260507-72@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260509
SUMMARY:Easy + Strides (Optional) (35-50 min easy)
DESCRIPTION:Optional easy run: 35-50 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:05-5:50/km) + 4-6x20s relaxed strides with full recovery. Skip if tired. Sunday remains the priority.
UID:20260509-73@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260510
SUMMARY:Long Run Easy (15-17 km after benchmark)
DESCRIPTION:Run 15-17 km easy (HR 135-150\, ~5:05-5:45/km). Keep this lighter after the 5K benchmark. No steady finish.
UID:20260510-74@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260512
SUMMARY:Aerobic Support + Short Steady (60-70 min total)
DESCRIPTION:15-20 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:05-5:45/km)\, then 20-30 min light steady (HR 150-158\, clearly below threshold)\, then easy running to 60-70 min total. If there is any lingering fatigue from May 7\, make the whole run easy and skip the steady block. Goal = support Thursday\, not compete with it.
UID:20260512-75@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260514
SUMMARY:Race-Pace Continuous (5-6 km controlled 10K effort)
DESCRIPTION:Warm-up 20 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:05-5:45/km) + 4 strides. Main: 5-6 km continuous at controlled 10K effort. First 2 km deliberately calm\, around ~4:04-4:06/km on flat calm terrain; only move toward ~4:00-4:03/km if you still feel smooth. If windy or HR surges unusually early\, convert to 2x3 km with 3 min easy jog. Cool-down 12-15 min easy. This is rhythm work\, not a time trial.
UID:20260514-76@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260517
SUMMARY:Long Run (14-16 km easy\, taper support)
DESCRIPTION:Taper long run: 14-16 km easy (HR 135-150\, ~5:05-5:45/km). No steady finish. Keep this smooth and unremarkable.
UID:20260517-77@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260519
SUMMARY:Easy + Strides (40-55 min easy)
DESCRIPTION:40-55 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:05-5:45/km) + 6x20s relaxed strides with full recovery. Goal = feel springy\, not tired.
UID:20260519-78@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260521
SUMMARY:Sharpener (3x1 km at controlled 10K pace)
DESCRIPTION:Warm-up 15-20 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:05-5:45/km) + 4 strides. Main: 3x1 km at controlled 10K pace\, roughly ~4:00-4:03/km\, with 3 min easy jog. Keep the first rep the easiest; finish feeling fresh enough that one more rep would be possible. Cool-down 12-15 min easy.
UID:20260521-79@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260523
SUMMARY:Easy + Strides (Optional) (30-45 min easy)
DESCRIPTION:Optional easy run: 30-45 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:10-5:50/km) + 4-6x20s relaxed strides only if you feel stale. Skip if there is any extra fatigue.
UID:20260523-80@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260524
SUMMARY:Long Run (12-14 km easy)
DESCRIPTION:Taper support run: 12-14 km easy (HR 135-150\, ~5:10-5:45/km). Prioritize recovery and freshness. No progression.
UID:20260524-81@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260526
SUMMARY:Easy + Strides (40-50 min easy)
DESCRIPTION:Taper week: 40-50 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:10-5:50/km) + 4-6x20s relaxed strides with full recovery. Keep the run boring and light.
UID:20260526-82@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260528
SUMMARY:Tune-up Fartlek (6x1 min at 10K effort)
DESCRIPTION:Warm-up 15 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:10-5:45/km). Main: 6x(1 min at controlled 10K effort / 90s easy jog). On flat calm ground the on-segments may land around ~3:58-4:05/km\, but keep them smooth and never all-out. Cool-down 10-15 min easy.
UID:20260528-83@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260531
SUMMARY:Pre-Race Easy (8-10 km easy + strides)
DESCRIPTION:Run 8-10 km easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:10-5:50/km) + 4x20s relaxed strides with full recovery. Stop while feeling fresh.
UID:20260531-84@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:Easy + Strides (35-40 min easy)
DESCRIPTION:35-40 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:10-5:50/km) + 4-6x20s relaxed strides. Keep legs awake and effort low.
UID:20260602-85@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260604
SUMMARY:Race-Week Sharpener (2x1.5 km at controlled 10K effort)
DESCRIPTION:Warm-up 15-20 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:10-5:50/km) + 4 strides. Main: 2x1.5 km at controlled 10K effort\, roughly ~4:00-4:03/km\, with 3 min easy jog. Do not race this workout. Finish confident and fresh. Cool-down 10-12 min easy.
UID:20260604-86@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260606
SUMMARY:Pre-Race Shakeout (20-30 min easy + strides)
DESCRIPTION:20-30 min easy (HR 130-145\, ~5:15-5:55/km) + 4x20s relaxed strides with full recovery. Keep it short\, calm\, and light.
UID:20260606-87@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260607
SUMMARY:10K Race / Time Trial (Sub-40 attempt)
DESCRIPTION:Warm-up 20 min easy (HR 135-148\, ~5:10-5:50/km) + drills + 4 strides. Race plan: first 2 km slightly conservative (~4:02-4:01/km or controlled effort)\, km 3-7 settle near goal effort (~4:00/km if breathing and form stay smooth)\, km 8-10 race by feel and squeeze only if still in control. In wind or on rolling ground\, protect effort rather than chasing exact splits. If you feel in trouble by 5 km\, reset for 1 km instead of forcing. Cool-down 10-15 min easy.
UID:20260607-88@10k-sub40
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
